EVE Online developer CCP Games is working with mobile game developer PlayRaven on a new project, reportedÂ The Verge. The developers are creating a mobile game called Project Aurora, which looks similar to the PC version of EVE Online and will feature similar game mechanics. Project Aurora will be a multiplayer title which sees players working together to dominate a multiplayer mobile universe. The game will launch globally in 2018. This follows EVE Online being changed to a free-to-play title by CCP Games.